items.text:
Volunteers Wanted - Liverpool Mystery Event

CAJ Productions is looking for 2 more reliable volunteers to help with a one-off mystery stunt in Liverpool City Centre on Saturday 20th September 2025.

It's part of a brand-new UK theatre tour coming in 2026, and this will be one of our headline public marketing stunts. 

The role is simple, but really important:

. Filming the event on a phone (1 person required)

. Guarding the event (managing livestream and any crowd that may form)

What you'll get:

. Travel covered

. Be part of an unusual, exciting event that's going to get a lot of attention

. Something different to talk about (and looks great on a CV for anyone in events, film, or theatre)

If you're free, reliable, and up for being part of something mysterious and fun, drop me a message here or comment below and I'll share the details.

Thanks! 

Charlie

Hey, I’m casting for a social-native, 6-part commercial series for a brand.

I am looking for actors of all genders, ages 23+ based in Liverpool. 

This will be filming in the coming weeks. Should you be cast in this specific commercial, filming will only be 1.5hours max. 

Non-professional actors encouraged😊

Please fill out this form to be considered, and I will be in contact asap with more details. 

Thanks,
Georgia

items.text:
Happy Wednesday, everyone! I am on the search for a Santa for this years Christmas at the Farm at The Hayloft

Casting breakdown:

"Christmas at the Farm," an immersive Santa's Grotto filled to the brim with excitement and adventure. Synopsis: Families join the Santa's crazy elves to learn the magic of an elf, help them make the reindeer food, and know why they feed their reindeer things like magic beans! They then join Santa, Mrs. Claus, and Elf Mittens for the short play before getting a professional photograph and being given a special gift by Mrs Claus. Oh! And there may be some pesky penguins about to cause extra mischief!

Santa 40+: The big man himself! Christmas cheer and joy, a man dedicated to bringing joy and peace to all. A bit of a goofball at times and adores his wife, elves and those pesky penguins. A joyous male-identifying actor to join the team for this year's Christmas celebrations. Ideally, the actor will have a real beard.

Dates: Rehearsals Nov. 21st, 22nd, and 23rd at the studio just outside of Liverpool City Centre. Show runs Dec. 6th, 7th, 13th, 14th, 20th, 21st, 22nd, 23rd,24th (early finish on 24; potential Dec. 18-19) at The Hayloft in Sandy Lane, Bold Heath, Great Sankey, Widnes, England

Pay: Rehearsals are paid at National Living Wage

Show days: £20.00 per hour, average of 8.5 hours a day.

Self Employed basis, we understand Christmas is a busy and can be an expensive time so we strive to have a very quick pay window so no one is waiting for wages over the Christmas period.

We are on the hunt for some elves, so if this interests you, please email me, and I can send you the details.

 

Please send CV/Spotlight or any questions to: erinhayloftevents@gmail.com

Warszawa! Na plan serialu Gliniarze poszukujemy epizodystów: 

Muras (20) - członek bandy Krzywego. „Kaskader” posiadający umiejętność wyczynowej jazdy na rowerze. Potrzebny na planie razem z rowerem - 22/23.10 - 1200 netto za całość

Sonik (20) - członek bandy Krzywego. „Kaskader” posiadający umiejętność wyczynowej jazdy na rowerze.  Potrzebny na planie razem z rowerem - 22/23.10 - 1200 netto za całość

Zgłoszenia proszę wysyłać na e-mail: a.fronczak.casting@gmail.com

W tytule maila proszę o wpisanie nazwy postaci.
W treści maila proszę o zawarcie następujących informacji:
1.           Wiek/wzrost/waga
2.           Nr tel. Do kontaktu
3.           Krótki opis doświadczenia
4.           Linki do sowich materiałów video – demo/wizytówka/scenki castingowe
5.           Aktualne zdjęcie

Nie zwracamy kosztów dojazdu/noclegu

Between Acts is a new theatre company based in Liverpool where we will be hosting cabaret nights with different performers and different themes each time. We’ll be releasing our very first casting call in a few weeks time so if you’d like to be a part of our first show, follow us on:

Instagram: @betweenacts_

Tiktok: @betweenacts_

Keep an eye out for the casting call and, in the mean time, take a look at our stories where we will be answering questions and taking suggestions for what themes you’d like to see!

Thanks all,

Niamh x

items.text:
ARE YOU AN ACTOR STUCK IN YOUR HEAD???

Yep... same. But I’ve been training with Steve Eastin and it’s honestly flipping everything upside down for me. You’ve seen this guy, he’s in like 200 movies [Catch Me If You Can, Con Air, Field of Dreams, Matchstick Men, etc.].

Not a lot of people even realize he’s teaching again. Feels like some random secret I lucked into.

What he does is just… different. Really different. Not about analyzing or breaking stuff down. It’s not gonna be for everyone but if you’re someone like me who gets trapped in overthinking, this is the kind of work that yanks you out of your head and dumps you right into the moment. If you live for those times where it feels like something else is taking over and you’re just along for the ride, this is that.

It’s rooted in Charles Conrad’s whole “choiceless awareness” thing. Basically stripping your brain of anything to hang onto and forcing you to just respond. No scene breakdowns, no making sure “beats” land. Just keeping it alive and messy and letting the work happen through you. If you’re curious, this article explains it better:

[[https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/](https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/)](https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/something-think-64356/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

Class is super bare bones. Sit across, cold read, memorize, toss it, repeat. Just working the muscle of not thinking. Everything’s filmed so you’re used to being on camera too.

And the wild part, Conrad literally handpicked Steve to carry this forward. He taught for decades, everyone in casting knew his people, then he retired. And now he just randomly opened these tiny classes at his house. They’re small, intimate, and honestly feel like something that shouldn’t still exist.

If this even slightly calls to you, it’s a rare shot.

Classes here:

[[https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/)](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

items.text:
SHOWCASE
Wow. What a day!

This lot were absolutely RUDDY MAGNIFICENT yesterday — they completely smashed it out of the park. Not only did they give fantastic performances, but the teamwork, support, and camaraderie between them all was just incredible. I’m beyond proud of every single one of them.

A huge thank you to everyone who came along to watch — from family and friends to members of the public and industry professionals. It was such a joy to hear all the fabulous feedback and to know how much everyone enjoyed the afternoon.

A special mention to Luna and Opal, who joined us as part of the production — two little stars who were fabulous and so professional.

We also had a bit of a Line of Duty reunion, with Bridgerton’s @claudia__jessie (Line of Duty series 4) and @gregssspiper (Line of Duty series 1, 4 & 5) coming along to support — such a treat to see them both!

And it was a real honour to have the wonderful Colin Edwards there with us too — my former drama teacher from ITV Workshop, and the inspirational person our scholarship is named after. Having him in the audience made the day even more special.

Finally, a heartfelt thank you for the incredible flowers, gifts, and card — I’m truly humbled. It’s such a privilege to work with such talented, kind, and generous people.

And a big shoutout to my lovely friend @corrangreen, who couldn’t be there but sent beautiful flowers to let me know she was thinking of us. A very special human ❤️

#theworkshopactorsstudio #theworkshop #birmingham #actingclass #showcase #actors #bridgerton #lineofduty #itvworkshop #colinedwards

items.text:
** **

**020 Mini serial wojenny 1940 historyczny z elementami Fantazy**

** **

**Kapłan świątyni Salomona mężczyzna**

 

Nasza Gliwicka Grupa Pasjonatów **‘’Morskie opowieści’’ **poszukuje mężczyzny  do roli kapłana świątyni Salomona . Najlepiej jakby kandydatka miała **od 50 – 30 lat** o szczupłej budowie ciała i wzroście 165/175** włosy koloru siwego bez żadnych tatuaży na twarzy z długą brodą. **Postać będzie występować w jednej scenie retrospekcji ze starożytności. Wymieniona scena będzie realizowana dopiero w lato ale już teraz szukamy kandydata.

 

Prosimy też o wysłanie aktualnych zdjęć. Szukamy kogoś z Gliwic lub okolic: Zabrze, Katowice najdalej. Same zdjęcia będą realizowane na terenie Gliwic.  Przedstawione powyżej materiały są z naszych sesji testowych.

 

**Na wiosnę roku 2026 planujemy realizacje zdjęc do tego **projektu. Będziemy realizować mini serial oparty o wątki grupy okultystycznej ’’**Ahnenerbe’**’ która chce zdobyć słynne artefakty ale w tym ktoś im chce przeszkadzać. Będziemy też sukcesywnie dodawać inne ogłoszenia związane z tym projektem. Mile widziane zdjęcia aktualne. Na zdjęciu powyżej osoba będzie mieć podobny kostium.** **Umieszczone materiały są z naszej sesji.** Nie będzie to zlecenie płatne.**

 

Więcej informacji na Priv

**Serial nie jest stworzony z sympatii do tej nazistowskiej organizacji lecz wynika to z samego scenariusza aby ukazał zbrodnie i sam fakt iż była w pełni zła. W produkcji znajdą się osoby, które będą chcieć walczyć i potępiać te wielkie zło jakim był nazizm. W oparciu o Dz.U.2017.0.2204 t.j. - Ustawa z dnia 6 czerwca 1997 r. - Kodeks karny,Art. 256 "Propagowanie faszyzmu lub innego ustroju totalitarnego lub nawoływanie domnienawiści", §3 - nie narusza prawa proponując przedmiot do celów historycznych lub kolekcjonerskich.**

items.text:
**Mini serial  wojenny 1940 – Kobieta, cywil francuski**

** **

Nasza Gliwicka Grupa Pasjonatów **‘’Grupa1940’’ ** kobietę  w wieku 25 – 30 do roli francuskiej kobiety. Postać kobiety będzie pokazana w jednym z odcinków podczas ataku Niemców na budynek cywilny. Razem z mężem będą chcieć uciekać z dymiącego się mieszkania. Oczywiście są przewidziane po 2 kwestie w jezyku francuskim. Zdjęcie poniżej jest naszym materiałem z testów tej sceny.

 

Szukamy osób beż tatuaży, bez farbowanych włosów czy długich paznokciach.  Jeśli chodzi o kostiumy to my je będziemy  wydawać.  Szukamy osób głównie z Gliwic i okolic (Zabrze, Katowice). Szukamy francuskich cywili, którzy będą atakowani przez niemiecki odział.

 

**Na wiosnę roku 2026 planujemy realizacje zdjęc do tego **projektu. Będziemy realizować mini serial oparty o wątki grupy okultystycznej ’’**Ahnenerbe’**’ która chce zdobyć słynne artefakty ale w tym ktoś im chce przeszkadzać. Będziemy też sukcesywnie dodawać inne ogłoszenia związane z tym projektem. Mile widziane zdjęcia aktualne. Na zdjęciu powyżej osoba będzie mieć podobny kostium.** **Umieszczone materiały są z naszej sesji.** Nie będzie to zlecenie płatne.**

 

Od 01.04.25 założyliśmy swój kanał na portalu youtube z filmami z naszych planów żeby można było zobaczyć jak to u nas wygląda od kuchni. 

 

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCE8KyfwpyFGzzwUDqdwy74g

 

**Nie będzie to zlecenie płatne.**

 

Więcej informacji na Priv

**Serial nie jest stworzony z sympatii do tej nazistowskiej organizacji lecz wynika to z samego scenariusza aby ukazał zbrodnie i sam fakt iż była w pełni zła. W produkcji znajdą się osoby, które będą chcieć walczyć i potępiać te wielkie zło jakim był nazizm. W oparciu o Dz.U.2017.0.2204 t.j. - Ustawa z dnia 6 czerwca 1997 r. - Kodeks karny,Art. 256 "Propagowanie faszyzmu lub innego ustroju totalitarnego lub nawoływanie domnienawiści", §3 - nie narusza prawa proponując przedmiot do celów historycznych lub kolekcjonerskich.**

sharedPost.text:
🚨 EXTRAS CASTING CALL 🚨

We are now casting for EXTRAS in our CRYPTO CORNER SCENE, where you will act as part of a crowd and gain the following:

✅ IMDb Credits
✅ Professional In Scene Stills/Photography for personal use
✅ The option for your in scene photos to be featured on our social media for promotional purposes

DISCLAMERS:
⚠️ We cast EXTRAS on a ONE TIME CAP, so please take note of this if you have worked as an extra with us before!
⚠️ This is an UNPAID opportunity 

We are FILMING 24th OCTOBER 2025 in HARROW ON THE HILL (specific location given to successful applicants) for 1-2pm

‼️ DEADLINE TO APPLY: 22nd OCTOBER 2025

To apply, please use this link:

https://screenliftstudios.co.uk/crew-%26-extras#2eae2a5a-6970-49e6-b0a7-9d7b20451a88

*All fields, including headshot submission, are compulsory - showreel NOT REQUIRED to be an extra

To find out more about SCREENLIFT’s TRAINING OPPORTUNITIES FOR CAST AND CREW, please visit:

https://screenliftstudios.co.uk/train-%26-get-cast

NO CACHEMENT AREA REQUIRED FOR SUBMISSIONS/INVOLVEMENT FOR EXTRAS AND TRAINING ACTORS - we look forward to hearing from you soon ❤️

items.text:
Pracownia Rysunku na Wydziale Malarstwa krakowskiej ASP poszukuje młodej modelki o szczupłej budowie ciała do pozowania w akcie (nago) studentom na zajęciach.

Zajęcia odbywają się trzy razy w tygodniu, od poniedziałku do środy w godz. 17.00-19.45 w gmachu głównym Akademii przy pl.Matejki 13. Podczas zajęć są trzy sesję. W trakcie każdej pozowanie trwa 45 min a następnie jest 15 min. przerwy.

W pracowni rysuje zazwyczaj kilka osób, w większości są to studentki. Atmosfera jest kameralna i bardzo przyjazna. Studenci i prowadzący są wyrozumiali wobec osób zaczynających swoją pracę w charakterze modela. Praca daje możliwość poznania ciekawych ludzi i bycie częścią społeczności ASP.

Stawka 30,50 zł/h brutto.

Zainteresowane osoby proszę o kontakt priv.

items.text:
Do 17 odcinka tego sezonu poszukuję osób do następujących ról:

1)Monika Winiarczyk (27) – wysportowana, zgrabna, włosy upięte w kucyk lub kok. Cicha, raczej introwertyczka. Bardzo inteligentna. Pracuje jako programistka. Ubrana wygodnie, ale zawsze estetycznie. Sceny: 1, 17, 23, 24 (łącznie 4 sceny)

Terminy: 1 dzień zdjęciowy: 24.10 (piątek)

Stawka: 450zł na rękę 

2)Jerzy Długosz (43) – ROLA DLA PROFESJONALNEGO AKTORA Z PRAWEM JAZDY. Właściciel firmy IT. Przeciętnego wzrostu i budowy ciała, chętnie z lekkimi zakolami. Modne dżinsy, trampki, drogi zegarek. Od lat prowadzi biznes, kiedyś dobrze zarabiał, ale sytuacja się ciągle pogarszała. Dlatego postanowił działać poza prawem, wpadł na pomysł hakowania i szantażowania większych, bogatszych firm. Jest zachłanny, dlatego dodatkowo zajął się również sprzedażą pornografii dziecięcej wykonanej z pomocą sztucznej inteligencji. Inteligentny, bez uczuć, skupiony na sobie.  

Sceny: 1, 5, 11, 13, 16A

Terminy: 2 dni zdjęciowe 23.10 i 24.10 (czwartek i Piątek) 

Stawka: 1200zł na rękę 

3)Maciek Mularski (31) – ROLA DLA PROFESJONALNEGO AKTORA Z PRAWEM JAZDY. Informatyk, programista. Bardzo inteligentny, świetny w swoich fachu, ale życiowo trochę nieporadny i naiwny. Nie zauważa, że Długosz coś przed nim ukrywa i w zasadzie to wykorzystuje go do tuszowania własnych przestępstw. Wysoki, dość masywny – ale raczej masa, a nie forma. Dżinsy, t-shirt z nadrukiem, sportowe buty.  

Sceny: 1, 11, 13, 17, 20, 21, 23, 24 – Wymagane PRAWO JAZDY

Terminy: 2 dni zdjęciowe 23.10 i 24.10 (czwartek i Piątek)

Stawka: 1200zł 

4)Paweł Jadczak (25-35) – pracownik Długosza. Informatyk, programista. Pracuje jeszcze dość krótko. Długosz nie wtajemniczył go w porwanie Moniki. Inteligentny, ale trochę chaotyczny. Ciemne spodnie, t-shirt, koszula w kratę, trampki. Sceny: 11, 13 

Terminy: 1 dzień zdjęciowy 23.10 (czwartek)

Stawka: 250zł na rękę 

5)Franciszek Piekarski (29) – Franek – były chłopak Moniki. Całkiem przystojny, bystry agent nieruchomości. Egoista, narcyz, lubi nadmierną kontrolę. Po rozstaniu czuł się zraniony i uważał, że Monika popełniła największy błąd swojego życia, bo nikogo lepszego nigdy nie znajdzie. Eleganckie spodnie, t-shirt, marynarka, mokasyny. Sceny: 7 TYLKO JEDNA SCENA!

Terminy: 1 dzień zdjęciowy 25.10 (sobota)

Stawka: 250zł na rękę 

Chętne osoby zapraszam do zgłoszenia się pod postem, oraz do wysyłania zgłoszeń na adres: natan.gliniarze@gmail.com

W tytule maila proszę o wpisanie nazwy postaci - można kilka, jeśli pasuje się do więcej niż jednej!!!!!

Bardzo ważne!!!

W treści maila proszę umieścić:

* linki do swoich materiałów video

* aktualne zdjęcie

* wiek, wzrost, wagę

* informacje o dotychczasowym doświadczeniu 

* oraz nr telefonu do kontaktu

Nie zwracamy kosztów dojazdu i noclegu.

Data: 14 i 15 października
Stawka: 900 zł netto za całość
 
2.           Kacper Sosnowski (20) –  Syn Sosnowskich. Student informatyki, nerd w okularach. Ubiera się w jeansy i polo. 
 
Data: 14  października
Stawka: 250 zł netto za całość
 
3.           Bartek Pawlik (21) – Kolega z uczelni Kacpra. Pewny siebie, wygadany. Ubiera się modnie. 
 
Data: 14  października
Stawka: 250 zł netto za całość
 
 
4.           Dawid Czerwiński (42) – pracuje jako Barman. Kochanek Sosnowskiej, z którą planuje przyszłość, gdy ta odejdzie od męża. Pewny siebie, opanowany. Ubiera się w czarne jeansy i czarne T-shirty. 

 
Data: 15  października
Stawka: 350 zł netto za całość
 
 
5.           Student (22) –  typ luzaka, ubiera się wygodnie.
 
Data: 14  października
Stawka: 200 zł netto za całość
 
6.           Siostra Pawłowskiej (50) – Starsza siostra ofiary, zatroskana i zaniepokojona. Sweter i sukienka, scena płaczu. 

 
Data: 13 października
Stawka: 250 zł netto
 
7.           Mikołaj Bielecki (45) – Były partner ofiary, diler z długami. Groził jej, że ją pobije w wyniku kłótni o pieniądze.

Data: 13 października
Stawka: 250 zł netto

 
8.           Zbychu „Ślepy” Wasiak (53) – Właściciel szemranego lombardu, który sprzedaj kradzione rzeczy. Typ sprzedawcy naciągacza, który słodzi w ofercie, a po wszystkim jest chamski i niemiły. Spodnie, rozpięta koszula i t-shirt 
 

Data: 14 października
Stawka: 450 zł netto
 
9.           Michalina Pawłowska (47) – Kobieta, która zostaje potrącona przez mężczyznę w hulajnodze. Ma przemocowego ex, ale sama z normalnego świata. 

 
Data: 13 października
Stawka: 250 zł netto

sharedPost.text:
CASTING  – rola główna w reklamie globalnej marki gamingowej

Szukamy wyjątkowego aktora męskiego do głównej roli w prestiżowym, międzynarodowym projekcie reklamowym związanym z gamingiem, reżyserowanym przez uznanego twórcę z Los Angeles.

Kogo szukamy:
Wiek: 55–75 lat
Etniczność: dowolna
Aktor o głębokiej emocjonalności i ekspresyjnej twarzy
Subtelna, ale wyrazista mimika i silne umiejętności aktorskie

Opis postaci:
Pokorny, samotny, nieoczekiwany – postać, która zostaje w pamięci. Poprzez drobne rytuały i gesty odkrywa tajemnice wirtualnych światów i pokazuje to, czego nikt inny nie dostrzega.

Casting:
Europejski + Wielka Brytania
Selftape / e-casting

Plan zdjęć:
Lokalizacja: Budapeszt
Podróż i przymiarki: 25–27 października
Zdjęcia: 28 października – 2 listopada

Wymagana dostępność w tym okresie

Po dodatkowe informacje prosimy zgłaszać się mailowo do WTORKU 7.10.2025r. do godz. 20:00, podając kod klienta, na adres:
📩 kariery@atvfilm.pl (w tytule maila wpisując: KONSOLA)

**CASTING KARMA DLA PSÓW**🐕‍🦺🐩
***Szukamy osób kochających pieski - będą sceny ze szczeniakami!***

**Wymagania ogólne (dla wszystkich Postaci):**
 - Różnorodność etniczna i kulturowa –  zależy nam, by obsada była reprezentatywna i rezonowała z odbiorcami na różnych rynkach.
 - Autentyczne, przyjazne uśmiechy i wyraziste twarze – ekspresja emocji i naturalność są kluczowe
- Szukamy ludzi, z którymi widz łatwo się utożsami.
- UWAGA! zgłaszający się, nie mogą mieć alergii na sierść!

1️⃣.  **Kobieta, ok 28–35 lat**
   - wszystkie kolory skóry
   - Naturalna uroda, przystępna, sympatyczna
   - Powinna umieć subtelnie przekazywać emocje i figlarność
   - Ciepło + odrobina wyrafinowania
    -Kochająca pieski

2️⃣. ** Kobieta, ok 30–40 lat**
    -Dowolne pochodzenie etniczne 
    -  Przyjazna, naturalna prezencja
    - Kochająca pieski

3️⃣.  **Mężczyzna, ok 28–35 lat**
   - Dowolne pochodzenie etniczne 
   -  „Chłopak z sąsiedztwa” – skromny, naturalny
   - Powinien potrafić przekazać emocje spojrzeniem
   - Autentyczny, oceniający
   -  Kochający pieski

📅**TERMINY:**
10.10.2025 RECALL WARSZAWA 
21.10.2025 PRZYMIARKI WARSZAWA 
23.10.2025 ZDJĘCIA WARSZAWA

LUB
2) CASTING ONLINE DO WTOREK 7.10

🚨 EXTRAS CASTING CALL 🚨

We are now casting for EXTRAS in our CRYPTO CORNER SCENE, where you will act as part of a crowd and gain the following:

✅ IMDb Credits
✅ Professional In Scene Stills/Photography for personal use
✅ The option for your in scene photos to be featured on our social media for promotional purposes

DISCLAMERS:
⚠️ We cast EXTRAS on a ONE TIME CAP, so please take note of this if you have worked as an extra with us before!
⚠️ This is an UNPAID opportunity 

We are FILMING 24th OCTOBER 2025 in HARROW ON THE HILL (specific location given to successful applicants) for 1-2pm

‼️ DEADLINE TO APPLY: 22nd OCTOBER 2025

To apply, please use this link:

https://screenliftstudios.co.uk/crew-%26-extras#2eae2a5a-6970-49e6-b0a7-9d7b20451a88

*All fields, including headshot submission, are compulsory - showreel NOT REQUIRED to be an extra

To find out more about SCREENLIFT’s TRAINING OPPORTUNITIES FOR CAST AND CREW, please visit:

https://screenliftstudios.co.uk/train-%26-get-cast

NO CACHEMENT AREA REQUIRED FOR SUBMISSIONS/INVOLVEMENT FOR EXTRAS AND TRAINING ACTORS - we look forward to hearing from you soon ❤️

SINGING LESSONS £60 hour

**First Session £10! **

- West End credited performer with 4 University degrees in teaching and voice and music. YOUR LIE IN APRIL, FROZEN, CYRANO DE BERGERAC, EVITA, THE KING AND I.

-Teaching in London out of Dance Attic Studios Fulham Broadway @danceatticstudios and ONLINE.

- Got recurring technical problems? Have you ever been told that certain genres and songs are just not for you? That your voice will always be a certain way? Have you ever left a singing lesson confused?

- Join the hundreds who have deliberately and conscientiously tackled their technique, and start building confidence today.

- Clients tend to have graduated from 3 year programs and leave with fundamental holes in their technique that they now want to fill. Is that you?

BOOK at www.chrisfung.co.uk

Chris Fung - Singing Teacher

items.text:
We’re on the lookout for some frightfully fun volunteers (or ghoulish gig-seekers!) to join us for our Halloween Spooky Walk at Trafford Waters Care Home on Thursday, 31st October at 5pm! 🕔

We're inviting anyone who loves Halloween and has a flair for the dramatic to be part of our spooky trail — just bring your own costume, makeup, and a good dose of spooky spirit!

✨ What you need to do:

Dress up in your best Halloween costume

Do your own makeup (creepy or kooky!)

Be ready to jump out and give our guests a little scare!

Be mindful that the event is open to the public, including children and older adults — so keep the scares fun, not frightening.

💸 This can be a paid role, or you’re welcome to volunteer — it’s entirely up to you!

📍 Location: Trafford Waters Care Home

🕔 Time: 5:00 PM

📅 Date: Friday, 31st October

Interested in joining our spooky crew? Drop us a message or leave a comment below! Let’s make this Halloween one to remember! 🦇💀

#HalloweenAtTraffordWaters #SpookyWalk #TraffordEvents #Halloween2025 #JoinTheScare

# 🌹 Master Social Media Post – IGNITE THE ROMANCE (Extended)

❤️ IGNITE THE ROMANCE ❤️
This photobook was more than a shoot – it was an emotional journey.

From the very first click of the camera, something shifted. The rain scenes weren’t just staged drama – the cold drops, the closeness of two people, the intensity of eye contact created a palpable electricity on set.

Between takes, there were moments of shared laughter, moments of quiet vulnerability, and an unspoken understanding: this wasn’t about pretending to be in love, but about channeling real human intimacy.

✨ Highlights of the shoot:

From the very first moment, the atmosphere shifted. The rain scenes weren’t just about water falling on fabric – they were about two people breathing in sync, skin chilled by the storm, eyes locked, hearts racing. The set went quiet, as if everyone was holding their breath with us.

Between takes, there was laughter, shared warmth, and a surprising tenderness. One moment, passion burned hot; the next, there was a fragile silence that made the chemistry even more powerful. These weren’t staged emotions – they were lived in the moment.

🎯 The goal of IGNITE THE ROMANCE:
To prove that I, Dan Martin Roesch, can embody the romantic leading man – not just through looks, but through real connection, vulnerability, and emotional depth.

🌍 Shared with my international film and casting community.

🤝 Proudly professionally represented, ready for productions worldwide.

🔗 IMDb: https://www.imdb.com/de/name/nm6401783/

items.text:
Bringing all the Performing Arts and associated businesses in one place. Working with smaller schools and studios across London and the UK to bring greater opportunities, higher standards, a brand new syllabus and quality education within the Arts and challenging the current way of how education and trades are taught for and within the industry. 
Please visit and follow #thecoventgardendanceandtheatreschool on FB and Istagram and the increasing number of feeder schools registered to it.

sharedPost.text:
Building something unique is exciting and, at times, very lonely. More to follow from London's West End and the real support I receive on a daily basis and what's happening next.
@thecoventgardendanceandtheatre is much more than a school!

🎭 FREE Introductory DRAMA Workshop For Young People In MANCHESTER This NOVEMBER 🎭

Join us at Red Players Academy for the FREE LAUNCH WORKSHOP of our BRAND NEW SATURDAY CLASS at our well-established and highly reputable drama school for young performers aged 9+

🌐 www.redplayersacademy.com/courses

🔴 RPA is Manchester’s elite-level drama school and talent agency – known for combining cutting-edge academic research with professional industry experience. Whether you’re just starting out or already experienced, our workshops are tailored to support every level!

🔴 We are an advanced training provider, offering advanced workshops in Acting, Drama, Movement, and Contemporary Performance. We teach all aspects of acting for both stage and screen, and are specialists in innovative and contemporary Creative Practice. 

🎬 Our students are currently appearing in:

📺 Netflix’s Adolescence
⚽ CBBC’s Jamie Johnson FC
🎭 13 Going on 30 @ Manchester Opera House
🔍 CBBC’s Odd Squad
…and more!

What you can expect at RPA:

🗓️Weekly Saturday classes in Altrincham
🎭 End-of-year showcase in a professional theatre
🎬 Acting for stage and screen
🎓 Taught by expert practitioners with 20+ years of experience
🌟 Curriculum is designed by acting coach & performance academic Lee Battle – credits include Coronation Street, Casualty, the BAFTA winning BBC drama The Street, Robin Hood, Awaydays and more
📣 Opportunity to join our SPOTLIGHT-registered Young Performers Talent Agency
🎬 Project-based, intensive, industry-focused learning environment

🗓️ LAUNCHING SATURDAY 1st NOVEMBER 2025

📍Limited spaces available – sign up to your FREE introductory workshop now!

📱 07441 396970
📧 info@redplayers.co.uk
🌐 www.redplayersacademy.com

Casting Call – Short Film (Title Productions)

Title Productions is currently casting for an upcoming short film. We are looking for a female actress, aged 20–30, with a slim build, based in Greater Manchester.
 • Shoot: One-day shoot
 • Auditions: This Wednesday (details will be provided upon selection)
 • Location: Greater Manchester

If this description matches you, please send an email to peshkorahim@icloud.com with your headshot (or a recent photo if you don’t have one), along with your name, age, and contact information.

We look forward to hearing from you!

Deividas Juo @deivjuo
Model | Performer | Wellness Professional
With over 50 professional photoshoots under my belt — including paid projects across fashion, lifestyle, artistic, body paint, and life modeling — I have developed a versatile presence in front of the camera backed by a disciplined lifestyle and unique skillset.

Alongside modeling, I bring on-screen experience from multiple TV shows, interview formats, podcasts, and extra appearances in my home country, while continuously expanding into acting and performance-based work.

Performance Skills
• Aerial Acrobatics — Hoop, Trapeze, Silks, Rope (Beginner–Intermediate)
• Contact Fire Staff — Intermediate
• Katana Wielding — Intermediate 
• Yoga — Advanced
• Swimming — Advanced
• Parkour - Intermediate
• Dancing - non professional but confident dancer

I’m currently seeking freelance work as model/actor/performer and agency representation (available internationally). Open to test shoots, collaborations, and paid opportunities.

✨ Updated measurements (as of Sept 22, 2025):
Height: 195cm
Chest: 41
Waist: 32
Hips: 37.5
Neck: 16
Sleeve: 32 (81.5cm)
Inseam: 32 (81.5cm)
Outseam: 36.4 (92.3cm)
Shoulder Width: 19 (48.5cm)
Shoe: UK 10.5 (can do 10–11) | EU 44–46

🌍 Based in London | Available worldwide

📲 Connect with me:
IG – @deivjuo

YouTube – @deivjuo

TikTok – @deivjuo

Looking forward to connecting

Professional Background
• Qualified Swimming Coach, Yoga Teacher, and Personal Trainer with 12+ years of teaching experience.
• Deep expertise in health, movement, breath, wellness, and high performance.

What Sets Me Apart
• Strong work ethic, relentless discipline, and ability to perform under discomfort, pressure, and challenging conditions.
• Holistic approach to self-regulation — always camera-ready, physically prepared, mentally sharp, and adaptable.
• Highly motivated in building my craft and presence — I create, edit, and post content daily across YouTube, TikTok, and Instagram to develop audience reach and on-camera charisma.

Current Focus
Seeking opportunities in modeling, acting, and performance — primarily in the UK (based in London ) but open to international projects. I’m committed to levelling up my skills, embracing bold creative challenges, and bringing exceptional authentic energy, professionalism, and reliability to every collaboration.

Kindest regards 
Deividas Juozapavičius
+12022558377
Instagram: @deivjuo
YouTube: @deivjuo
TikTok: @deivjuo

Hi everyone, I'm Deividas 30, Lithuanian.

Model | Performer | Wellness Professional
With over 50 professional photoshoots under my belt — including paid projects across fashion, lifestyle, artistic, body paint, and life modeling — I have developed a versatile presence in front of the camera backed by a disciplined lifestyle and unique skillset.

Link below intro video
https://drive.google.com/file/d/19OcejTSRFWF2ZmQxdeoF92CEF7TKKAdb/view?usp=drivesdk

Alongside modeling, I bring on-screen experience from multiple TV shows, interview formats, podcasts, and extra appearances in my home country, while continuously expanding into acting and performance-based work.

Performance Skills
• Aerial Acrobatics — Hoop, Trapeze, Silks, Rope (Beginner–Intermediate)
• Contact Fire Staff — Intermediate
• Katana Wielding — Intermediate 
• Yoga — Advanced
• Swimming — Advanced
• Parkour - Intermediate
• Dancing - non professional but confident dancer

I’m currently seeking freelance work as model/actor/performer and agency representation (available internationally). Open to test shoots, collaborations, and paid opportunities.

✨ Updated measurements (as of Sept 22, 2025):
Height: 195cm
Chest: 41
Waist: 32
Hips: 37.5
Neck: 16
Sleeve: 32 (81.5cm)
Inseam: 32 (81.5cm)
Outseam: 36.4 (92.3cm)
Shoulder Width: 19 (48.5cm)
Shoe: UK 10.5 (can do 10–11) | EU 44–46

🌍 Based in London | Available worldwide

Professional Background
• Qualified Swimming Coach, Yoga Teacher, and Personal Trainer with 12+ years of teaching experience.
• Deep expertise in health, movement, breath, wellness, and high performance.

What Sets Me Apart
• Strong work ethic, relentless discipline, and ability to perform under discomfort, pressure, and challenging conditions.
• Holistic approach to self-regulation — always camera-ready, physically prepared, mentally sharp, and adaptable.
• Highly motivated in building my craft and presence — I create, edit, and post content daily across YouTube, TikTok, and Instagram to develop audience reach and on-camera charisma.

Current Focus
Seeking opportunities in modeling, acting, and performance — primarily in the UK (based in London ) but open to international projects. I’m committed to levelling up my skills, embracing bold creative challenges, and bringing exceptional authentic energy, professionalism, and reliability to every collaboration.

If you need anything else please let me know 

Kindest regards 
Deividas Juozapavičius
+12022558377
Instagram: @deivjuo
YouTube: @deivjuo
TikTok: @deivjuo

We're casting for our magical Christmas Grotto experience in the Milton Keynes and Bedford area and we’re on the lookout for a charismatic, professional Mother Christmas to join the team!

📍 Location: 2 venues across MILTON KEYNES & BEDFORD
MK44 3QP & MK17 8UE
📆 Contract: December 2025
💸 Rate: £20 per hour

✨ Requirements:

• Entry-level acting skills

• Basic script work and immersive performance ability

• Confident group singing of children’s Christmas songs

• Must absolutely love Christmas!

You’ll be part of a heartwarming festive experience for families and children, in a beautifully themed setting. 

🧝‍♀️ We’re looking for:

• Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

• Friendly, reliable team players

• Previous experience working with children or in character-based roles is a plus

📌 Important Info:

• Costume and full training provided

• Paid rehearsals and site visits will be scheduled in early November – exact dates TBC

• Below is the confirmed list of working dates and shift times:

Tue, Dec 2 – 1:30 PM to 7:00 PM

Thu, Dec 4 – 1:30 PM to 6:00 PM

Tue, Dec 9 – 10:30 AM to 5:00 PM

Tue, Dec 16 – 10:30 AM to 7:00 PM

Fri, Dec 19 – 8:30 AM to 6:00 PM

Sat, Dec 20 – 8:30 AM to 6:00 PM

📩 To apply:
Send your CV, headshot, and any relevant performance footage to: castings@evokeents.com
Subject line: MOTHER CHRISTMAS CONTRACT
Tell us a little about why you’d be a great fit & the dates you're interested in working — we’d love to hear from you!

items.text:
CASTING CALL

Production Company: GreenHouse Films Production

Project Type: BFA Short Film

Union Status: Non-Union

Pay Status: Unpaid Projected

Shooting Dates: TBD

Shooting Location: Orlando area

Summary: A lonely girl shunned by her school finds comfort in plants and in the one friend who truly sees her.

We have not set an exact shoot date, but we plan to begin filming sometime in November. This is an unpaid project - copy and credit will be given to all involved. This is a non-union production.

Character Breakdowns:

MONOMAY: Female, Late Teens (20s), A teen girl marked by facial scars and iris coloboma, finds purpose and comfort in tending to her beloved plants.

JASON: Male, Late Teens (20s), The school's "Golden Boy" athlete, hides his insecurities behind charisma.

FAN CLUB: Any gender, Teens (20s), A group of students that fawn over Jason and seek his attention.

How to Submit: Please send an email to greenhousefilmsproduction@gmail.com to reserve a time slot for auditions.

items.text:
Casting call · 04.10 · 14:00–16:00 · Kraków

When and where: October 4, 14:00–16:00, Kraków, Romanowicza 19b. 

The project: student independent short film, prepared for submission to European festivals and media exposure.
Plot: action takes place 30 years from our time; a dystopia about the "oppression" of the body and rebellion against a repressive regime.
Who do you work with: a professional team led by director
What the artists will get: promotion in our social networks, the opportunity to use filmed materials in the portfolio, visibility at European festivals.
The film is independent - payment for shifts is not provided, agreement on commissions in case of success of the film and awards.
Organizer: Theatre studio "Bez Uprzedzeń" (NIP 6793287079).
Filming: 2–3 shifts in the window of October 15–31, 2025 (exact dates to be confirmed).

We are careful about the topic of the film and the boundaries of the artists: any sensitive actions (for example, a kiss) - only with your express consent, under safe conditions. No nudity without separate agreement. There is zero tolerance for harassment and discrimination on the site. 

Who are we looking for?
The main roles:
- Female, 20–30 years old. Height 160–175, clothing size S–M. Natural European appearance, feminine. Blonde/brown/light shoulder-length hair or longer, straight or wavy. The eyes are light or light brown. Fluent  English required
- Male, 20–30 years old. Height 178–195, athletic physique (natural dramatik appearance). Short dark blond or dark hair, straight or with a slight wave. No beard or with light facial hair. Fluent  English required
- Male, 25–40 years old. Slender, possible androgynous type. An expressive gaze and mimics, large eyes, dark haired. Preferably clean shaven. Visible tattoos/piercings are allowed (moderately).

Episodes / Cameos:
- Woman, 20–35 years old. Height 165–180, "dramatic" type: expressive green or dark brown eyes, full lips, dark/black hair.
- Dancers (4 performers): Women with good plasticity; the ability to improvise to club music solo and in interaction.
Group of club visitors (5 performers):
- 3 men 30–50 — strong physique, pronounced natural hair is allowed.
- 2 women 20–30 — short, slender, elegant constitution.
- male couple (2 performers), comfortable with interaction on the camera, including a screen kiss (with your consent).

items.summary:
Casting call · 04.10 · 14:00–16:00 · Kraków

When and where: October 4, 14:00–16:00, Kraków, Romanowicza 19b. 

The project: student independent short film, prepared for submission to European festivals and media exposure.
Plot: action takes place 30 years from our time; a dystopia about the "oppression" of the body and rebellion against a repressive regime.
Who do you work with: a professional team led by director
What the artists will get: promotion in our social networks, the opportunity to use filmed materials in the portfolio, visibility at European festivals.
The film is independent - payment for shifts is not provided, agreement on commissions in case of success of the film and awards.
Organizer: Theatre studio "Bez Uprzedzeń" (NIP 6793287079).
Filming: 2–3 shifts in the window of October 15–31, 2025 (exact dates to be confirmed).

We are careful about the topic of the film and the boundaries of the artists: any sensitive actions (for example, a kiss) - only with your express consent, under safe conditions. No nudity without separate agreement. There is zero tolerance for harassment and discrimination on the site. 

Who are we looking for?
The main roles:
- Female, 20–30 years old. Height 160–175, clothing size S–M. Natural European appearance, feminine. Blonde/brown/light shoulder-length hair or longer, straight or wavy. The eyes are light or light brown. Fluent  English required
- Male, 20–30 years old. Height 178–195, athletic physique (natural dramatik appearance). Short dark blond or dark hair, straight or with a slight wave. No beard or with light facial hair. Fluent  English required
- Male, 25–40 years old. Slender, possible androgynous type. An expressive gaze and mimics, large eyes, dark haired. Preferably clean shaven. Visible tattoos/piercings are allowed (moderately).

Episodes / Cameos:
- Woman, 20–35 years old. Height 165–180, "dramatic" type: expressive green or dark brown eyes, full lips, dark/black hair.
- Dancers (4 performers): Women with good plasticity; the ability to improvise to club music solo and in interaction.
Group of club visitors (5 performers):
- 3 men 30–50 — strong physique, pronounced natural hair is allowed.
- 2 women 20–30 — short, slender, elegant constitution.
- male couple (2 performers), comfortable with interaction on the camera, including a screen kiss (with your consent).
A couple with a performative BDSM image (2 performers):
- The dominant figure - tall, large; any age/gender; comfortable wearing heels/platform shoes.
- Submissive partner - possible representation in latex and a mask (including a stylized one). Only with full consent, without dangerous practices; closed playground; interactions are agreed in advance.

items.text:
CASTING CALL - PRESENTER FOR SOCIAL MEDIA CAMPAIGN FOR FINANCIAL SERVICES COMPANY IN LONDON (POTENTIALLY 13th OCTOBER)

Hi all, we’re currently casting for a presenter for a short social media video with us. We’re looking for someone with experience presenting, who can share links for us to review.

We’re hoping for someone with bags of personality who’s happy and confident to approach people in the street and stoke up a conversation, but you’ll also be required to deliver a piece to camera. You’d need to be very confident riding a bike and have a decent level of fitness, as we’ll be following you cycle around London for a couple of hours on a branded bike.

Please only send on details if you have Presenting experience, with links to recent work. Email details to casting@feral-films.com. Please do not DM me, only send details via email.

This is a paid role, with travel (to and from the location within London) and sustenance all covered on the shoot.

The shoot date is pencilled for the 13th October, this may change however. The location is likely to be Central London. 

Thank you!

Gulliver’s Theme Park Resorts are on the talent hunt for talented individuals to join our thrilling and magical experiences!  Fright Fiesta Halloween & Festive Christmas Casting Opportunities.

CASTING FOR: DANCERS, SCARE ACTORS, STREET THEATRE ENTERTAINERS, ELVES AND STAGE PRESENTERS

OPEN AUDITION, GULLIVER'S WORLD, WARRINGTON

SATURDAY 27TH SEPTEMBER, Gulliver's World Resort Hotel, Shackleton Close, Warrington, WA5 9YZ.  Registration at 17.30pm.  

Report to the hotel reception with your CV.  Please come with suitable attire to dance.  Free car parking available on site.  If you cannot make the audition date but are interested in winter opportunities, please email Casting with your CV.

Scare Actors: Bring our family scare attractions to life by delivering spine-tingling thrills and fun.

Street Theatre Entertainers: Delivering spooky fun and festive cheer, captivating guests with your improvisation and character creation skills. If you have any circus skills or stilt experience this would advantageous. 

Dancers: Shine in our daytime and evening shows for Halloween & Christmas

Actors & Puppeteers: Animate our stage shows and immersive experiences, making stories come alive with your performance

Elves: Create unforgettable moments in our grotto experience, spreading holiday joy as Santa’s helpers.

Santa: To bring alive the Christmas cheer in our grottos making a magical experience for the whole family.  Rates up to £20 per hour.

Contracts Available from Late September to 1st January 2026 with flexible working hours. If you are interested in opportunities at Gulliver's Valley, Rotherham, Gulliver's Land Milton Keynes please email your CV highlighting which Resort you are interest in.

casting@gulliversfun.co.uk

CASTING CALL – TaleGate Theatre: Winter Wonderland Workshop

LOCATION: Attwell Farm Park, Redditch (West Midlands, UK)
PRODUCTION DATES:

• Auditions: 8 October 2025

• Rehearsals: 17–18 November 2025

• Performances:

◦ 29–30 November

◦ 6–7 December

◦ 13–14 December

◦ 19–24 December 2025

PAID, UNPAID OR PROFIT SHARE: Paid – £130 per day
PRODUCER OR PRODUCTION COMPANY: TaleGate Theatre Productions

CASTING BRIEF – CHRISTMAS IMMERSIVE EXPERIENCE

TaleGate Theatre are looking for talented and enthusiastic performers (18+) to bring their Winter Wonderland Workshop to life for families this Christmas at Attwell Farm Park.

This magical project will transform six themed spaces into an immersive world of pantomime-inspired storytelling, playful character encounters, and interactive improvisation. Performers must be comfortable improvising, connecting with children and families, and working collaboratively to create unforgettable holiday memories.

Applicants must be local or able to commute to Redditch and available for all listed dates.

HOW TO APPLY:

Apply for this casting as a Talent PRO member at Actors and Extras with a 1-month FREE trial period.� Visit [https://actorsandextras.com/casting-calls](https://actorsandextras.com/casting-calls?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExcnBidGF3WEppZmRzM3N6awEeQzO1BBFjiRr1eWHhwMrb2FOklVKZdRyGKd2hA2144B720mDTUEWFJoHLlUc_aem_ubS900BdXqg3eH4a8vEBlw)

items.text:
Gm, wanted to invite all to a great Casting Call Happening October 18th!! More information below! Please comment below if you can come! W Talent NYC would love to see you there!..

DEAR INVITED TALENT, 

We would like to invite you to our NEXT OPEN CALL session on SATURDAY, OCTOBER 18th, 3PM (SHARP) at 447 West 36th Street, New York, NY.
* The HUDSON YARDS LOFT. STUDIO 4. 

PLEASE ARRIVE AT 2:30PM TO REGISTER.

We are currently CASTING for ZARA kids, THE GAP kids, and multiple TV/Film projects for NETFLIX (Non-Union) as well as Fashion Weeks in the following Countries:
New York Fashion Week:  February 12 - 17, 2026 in NYC. 
Depending on the Project, Payrate will vary:

ADULT PAY RATE: $1000/day - $8000/day (18+)
TEEN PAY RATE: $1000/day - $5000/day (13 - 17)
CHILDREN PAY RATE: $800/day - $2500/day (ages 2 - 12)

MUST BRING A PRINTED OUT PHOTO (8x10) simple snapshot/selfie, OR Acting Headshot/Resume, OR YOUR MODEL COMPOSITE CARD.  Any of these are fine.

Please respond to this message to confirm your attendance with "Will be attending". 

Please keep this DATE/TIME/LOCATION on your calendar. We do NOT send out reminders. 

Open Calls will last approximately 1.5 hour.

Actors - Please have a 60 second monologue to perform. No swearing. No political,  No sexual, or religious content, please. 

Female Models - Please wear heels to perform a videotaped Runway Walk and wear a form-fitting all black outfit.

Male Models - Please wear jeans and a form-fitting t-shirt.

Children: Please wear casual/comfortable outfits.

items.text:
We're casting for our magical Christmas Grotto experience in the Milton Keynes and Bedford area and we’re on the lookout for a charismatic, professional Mother Christmas to join the team!

📍 Location: 2 venues across MILTON KEYNES & BEDFORD
MK44 3QP & MK17 8UE
📆 Contract: December 2025
💸 Rate: £20 per hour

✨ Requirements:

• Entry-level acting skills

• Basic script work and immersive performance ability

• Confident group singing of children’s Christmas songs

• Must absolutely love Christmas!

You’ll be part of a heartwarming festive experience for families and children, in a beautifully themed setting. 

🧝‍♀️ We’re looking for:

• Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

• Friendly, reliable team players

• Previous experience working with children or in character-based roles is a plus

📌 Important Info:

• Costume and full training provided

• Paid rehearsals and site visits will be scheduled in early November – exact dates TBC

• Below is the confirmed list of working dates and shift times:

Tue, Dec 2 – 1:30 PM to 7:00 PM

Thu, Dec 4 – 1:30 PM to 6:00 PM

Tue, Dec 9 – 10:30 AM to 5:00 PM

Tue, Dec 16 – 10:30 AM to 7:00 PM

Fri, Dec 19 – 8:30 AM to 6:00 PM

Sat, Dec 20 – 8:30 AM to 6:00 PM

📩 To apply:
Send your CV, headshot, and any relevant performance footage to: castings@evokeents.com
Subject line: MOTHER CHRISTMAS CONTRACT
Tell us a little about why you’d be a great fit & the dates you're interested in working — we’d love to hear from you!

items.text:
Exciting News! Following the incredible success of our award-winning short film 'The Hit' at the Short Film Festival Manchester, Marble Academy and Solefuge Media Productions are thrilled to announce auditions for our upcoming low-budget short film, ‘Hotel Rent,’ set to film early next year.

We're on the lookout for six talented actors to bring this project to life! While these roles are unpaid, we will cover travel expenses and provide meals. 
Plus, this is a fantastic opportunity to enhance your showreel or portfolio!

If you’re passionate about acting and eager to dive into a vibrant creative environment, we want to hear from you! 
Please send us a direct message or an email to marbleacademy@hotmail.com. Share a bit about yourself, the role that excites you the most, and what draws you to that character.
Auditions are in-person on Saturday, November 22nd, in Swinton, Manchester.

Don’t forget to include a link to your Spotlight or Backstage profile. We can’t wait to find the incredible talent that will shine in our project!

items.text:
🎭 Performers Wanted – Play Elsa or Santa This Christmas with Bunny Business Events! 🎅❄️

Bunny Business Events is casting for two magical roles to join our team this festive season:

✨ Elsa – The Snow Queen

We’re looking for a confident, charismatic performer to bring Elsa to life at children’s parties, Christmas events and seasonal celebrations. Singing ability is a huge bonus (but not essential) – what matters most is your ability to engage, enchant and command the room. You’ll make magical memories for children and families, creating unforgettable moments through storytelling, games, photos, and more. This is an ongoing role into 2026 with consistent, frequent weekend work.

🎅 Santa Claus

We’re also seeking a warm, jolly performer to step into the iconic red suit this Christmas! As Santa, you’ll spread festive cheer, meet and greet families and deliver magical experiences at grottos, parties and corporate events. Age-appropriate appearance for the role is required.

💰 Pay: £30 – £50 per hour (depending on event and experience)

📅 When: Frequent and flexible work across weekends, school holidays and the run-up to Christmas

📍 Where: Events across Greater Manchester, South Manchester, Cheshire, and Warrington – you must live within comfortable travelling distance of SK9 postcode

🌟 We’re Looking For:

Confident, fun, and engaging performers who can command a room

Strong with children and families – warm, approachable and full of energy

Experience in performing arts, acting or entertainment is advantageous

Must drive and have your own transport (travel costs subsidised)

Weekend and festive season availability is essential

🎁 What We Offer:

All costume, props, and training provided

Flexible, frequent bookings with excellent pay

A fun, rewarding opportunity to bring joy and magic to children during the most wonderful time of the year

📩 How to Apply:

Send your CV and a recent headshot to hello@bunnybusinessevents.co.uk

📱 Follow us on social media: Bunny Business Events

Muras (20) - członek bandy Krzywego. „Kaskader” posiadający umiejętność wyczynowej jazdy na rowerze. Potrzebny na planie razem z rowerem - 22/23.10 - 1200 netto za całość

Sonik (20) - członek bandy Krzywego. „Kaskader” posiadający umiejętność wyczynowej jazdy na rowerze.  Potrzebny na planie razem z rowerem - 22/23.10 - 1200 netto za całość

Zgłoszenia proszę wysyłać na e-mail: a.fronczak.casting@gmail.com

W tytule maila proszę o wpisanie nazwy postaci.
W treści maila proszę o zawarcie następujących informacji:
1.           Wiek/wzrost/waga

3.           Krótki opis doświadczenia
4.           Linki do sowich materiałów video – demo/wizytówka/scenki castingowe
5.           Aktualne zdjęcie

items.text:
Artistic Proposal – Cía. Báscula
Show: "Jumping Stars"�Discipline: Korean Teeterboard

Company Introduction
We are Cía. Báscula, a contemporary circus company specializing in Korean teeterboard, composed of artists trained at the National University of San Martín (Argentina). Our work blends high-level acrobatics with a contemporary stage language, adaptable to diverse contexts and audiences.
We would love the opportunity to present our show "Jumping Stars" as part of your circus show.

Technical Requirements – Rider for "Jumping Stars"
Stage Space Requirements:
* Minimum dimensions: 3 meters (width) x 6 meters (depth)
* Minimum height clearance: 6 meters
* Surface: flat and stable, with at least 1 m² of level ground to install the teeterboard system. If the ground is uneven, it is sufficient to level the area where the board will be placed.
Teeterboard Specifications:
* Dimensions: 3.15 meters long x 45 cm wide
* Material: hard, flexible wood (preferably Guatambú, Brazilian Lapacho, or French Ash)
Lighting:
* Minimum requirement: general lighting, adaptable for both indoor and outdoor settings
* Colored lights may be used – no complex lighting design is necessary
Sound:
* The company provides 3 audio tracks for the performance
* Requirements:
    * At least 2 speakers or amplifiers (200W minimum)
    * 1 sound technician to play the tracks according to our cues
Setup and Takedown:
* Setup time: approx. 15 minutes (on the day of the performance)
* Takedown and loading: approx. 15 minutes after the show
Loading and Unloading:
* The company will handle loading and unloading of its equipment
* It is essential that the transport vehicle can access the performance area as closely as possible

Video Material
https://youtu.be/-AKUqShvQUs?si=wweW-faS-UAPChNf

Social Media
* Instagram:�@cia.bascula�@acrobate.ar�@lauguatojp�@morenieves_

Show: "Jumping Stars"�Discipline: Korean Teeterboard

Company Introduction
We are Cía. Báscula, a contemporary circus company specializing in Korean teeterboard, composed of artists trained at the National University of San Martín (Argentina). Our work blends high-level acrobatics with a contemporary stage language, adaptable to diverse contexts and audiences.
We would love the opportunity to present our show "Jumping Stars" as part of your circus show.

Technical Requirements – Rider for "Jumping Stars"
Stage Space Requirements:
* Minimum dimensions: 3 meters (width) x 6 meters (depth)
* Minimum height clearance: 6 meters
* Surface: flat and stable, with at least 1 m² of level ground to install the teeterboard system. If the ground is uneven, it is sufficient to level the area where the board will be placed.
Teeterboard Specifications:
* Dimensions: 3.15 meters long x 45 cm wide
* Material: hard, flexible wood (preferably Guatambú, Brazilian Lapacho, or French Ash)
Lighting:
* Minimum requirement: general lighting, adaptable for both indoor and outdoor settings
* Colored lights may be used – no complex lighting design is necessary
Sound:
* The company provides 3 audio tracks for the performance
* Requirements:
    * At least 2 speakers or amplifiers (200W minimum)
    * 1 sound technician to play the tracks according to our cues
Setup and Takedown:
* Setup time: approx. 15 minutes (on the day of the performance)
* Takedown and loading: approx. 15 minutes after the show
Loading and Unloading:
* The company will handle loading and unloading of its equipment
* It is essential that the transport vehicle can access the performance area as closely as possible

Video Material
https://youtu.be/-AKUqShvQUs?si=wweW-faS-UAPChNf

Social Media
* Instagram:�@cia.bascula�@acrobate.ar�@lauguatojp�@morenieves_

We’re looking for the final few performers to fulfil contracts at a top Liverpool attraction this Halloween and Christmas!

🎃 HALLOWEEN – 25th Oct to 2nd Nov 🎃

🎅🏼 Looking for a warm, friendly Father Christmas performer (Maggie Beard and Heidi Suit provided!) and several grotto elves to bring the festive fun.

💰 Competitive day rates that vary for each role / contract.

📧 If interested in either, please email Sam@LaughingBulldogEvents.co.uk with which role you’re interested in, availability, and a recent photo of yourself.

Gulliver’s Theme Park Resorts are on the talent hunt for talented individuals to join our thrilling and magical experiences!  Fright Fiesta Halloween & Festive Christmas Casting Opportunities.

CASTING FOR: DANCERS, SCARE ACTORS, STREET THEATRE ENTERTAINERS, ELVES AND STAGE PRESENTERS

OPEN AUDITION, GULLIVER'S WORLD, WARRINGTON

SATURDAY 27TH SEPTEMBER, Gulliver's World Resort Hotel, Shackleton Close, Warrington, WA5 9YZ.  Registration at 17.30pm.  

Report to the hotel reception with your CV.  Please come with suitable attire to dance.  Free car parking available on site.  If you cannot make the audition date but are interested in winter opportunities, please email Casting with your CV.

Scare Actors: Bring our family scare attractions to life by delivering spine-tingling thrills and fun.

Street Theatre Entertainers: Delivering spooky fun and festive cheer, captivating guests with your improvisation and character creation skills. If you have any circus skills or stilt experience this would advantageous. 

Dancers: Shine in our daytime and evening shows for Halloween & Christmas

Actors & Puppeteers: Animate our stage shows and immersive experiences, making stories come alive with your performance

Elves: Create unforgettable moments in our grotto experience, spreading holiday joy as Santa’s helpers.

Santa: To bring alive the Christmas cheer in our grottos making a magical experience for the whole family.  Rates up to £20 per hour.

Contracts Available from Late September to 1st January 2026 with flexible working hours. If you are interested in opportunities at Gulliver's Valley, Rotherham, Gulliver's Land Milton Keynes please email your CV highlighting which Resort you are interest in.

casting@gulliversfun.co.uk

items.text: Looking for acting jobs in and around Liverpool i Would like to start a career in acting

topComments.text:
Do you have training? Headshots? Showreel? On Spotlight? 
A Director I know had 5300 applications via Spotlight for a short film she’s making. There are so many talented people but so many talented, trained people with a fab range of headshots who are struggling to get auditions. That’s not to say it’s impossible but start with training, apply to agencies, do some am-dram, get together some showreels to show CDs what you can do. Follow CD instagrams so you know when they are looking for your casting type. You obviously can’t just start a career but with years of work doing the above you will hopefully get seen. Good luck.
You gotta look out for casting calls, unless you are an a lister, nobody comes to you, you have to find them.

Философия жизни - тот отрезок незаметный.

И мне неважно хорошо или плохо о бомне скажут. Главное что я достоин перед самим собой.

items.text:
Witam.
Chłopak lat 18 z 3 letnim doświadczeniem jako mechanik samochodowych, chętnie spróbowałby czegoś nowego, 
Aktualnie jestem w trakcie wykonywania szkoły średniej.
Nie mam zaliczonych żadnych kursów/szkół aktorskich, jestem amatorem w tej kwestii, nie mam żadnych doświadczeń.
Ogólnie jestem osobą która żadnych nowych rzeczy i doświadczeń się nie boi, więc jestem w stanie dostosować się do każdej roli.
Mogę dojechać na casting/spotkanie w promieniu 100km od Ostrowa Wielkopolskiego.
Jeśli będzie ktoś zainteresowany kontaktem ze mną to zapraszam do pozostawienia komentarza.
Durne i niepotrzebne komentarze proszę sobie darować.

Witam.
Chłopak lat 18 z 3 letnim doświadczeniem jako mechanik samochodowych, chętnie spróbowałby czegoś nowego, 
Aktualnie jestem w trakcie wykonywania szkoły średniej.
Nie mam zaliczonych żadnych kursów/szkół aktorskich, jestem amatorem w tej kwestii, nie mam żadnych doświadczeń.
Ogólnie jestem osobą która żadnych nowych rzeczy i doświadczeń się nie boi, więc jestem w stanie dostosować się do każdej roli.
Mogę dojechać na casting/spotkanie w promieniu 100km od Ostrowa Wielkopolskiego.
Jeśli będzie ktoś zainteresowany kontaktem ze mną to zapraszam do pozostawienia komentarza.
Durne i niepotrzebne komentarze proszę sobie darować.

items.text:
🚨CASTING ACTORS for a dark arthouse short film "Dollface"🚨

Date :2-3 days between Oct 22nd-28th.

Location: Los Angeles CA

Rate: Non union, Low budget and unpaid. Here is what I can offer!

Full film credit , Reel material, Festival submissions, Super cool vibe with a cool, dark story😎

Project: This is a passion project of mine. The film explores the dark underbelly of hustler sexwork.  When one of two best friends goes missing after a night of working, a male hustler seeks revenge on the person who took his friend's life. It is dark and provocative and pushes boundaries.

 

Roles: 

Francesca (Principal Female 20s)- She is bold and confident, bit of a firecracker, reckless. (Must be comfortable with smoking a prop cigarette and wearing semi revealing clothes as she is in the sexwork industry)

John (Principal 27-30s)  - Stone cold. Blunt. Sleezy. He picks up a male sex worker and takes him to a motel in exchange for a good night. (Must be comfortable being semi nude, and doing simulated sexual activities. NO SEX SCENES)

Murderer (Principal 25-37)- Seemingly normal. Respectful and friendly but it's all a facade. He picks up hustlers and is responsible for their brutal fate. 

Please ask me if you have any questions! If actors would like, intimacy coordinator will be present. 

Casting from self tapes! Please email me with a headshot, resume and reel (if applicable) to marcoroni2003@gmail.com

We are looking for talents for a social media video of a downtown street food restaurant.

* Female, 25–32 years old, blonde, dark blonde or red hair, Scandinavian type
* Male, 25–32 years old, blonde, dark blonde or red hair, Scandinavian type

**Shooting date:** October 13, 2025 (Monday)
**Location:** Budapest
**Duration:** approx. half day
**Fee:** 40,000 HUF

**Usage:** Online, social media, website

Please send your application to **futurecastingbp@gmail.com** with the following details:

**Subject:** Street Food
* Name
* Age
* Phone number
* One close-up portrait (preferably front view)
* One full-body photo
*

Thank you,
Future Casting

items.text:
My name is Adelola Mary Haastrup, and I’m a passionate actress currently based in Nigeria. I’m looking to expand my career in the UK and am actively seeking opportunities for visa sponsorship.

I started acting at the age of 7, performing in stage productions. While much of my early work was in gospel theater, I’m not particularly religious, and my focus has always been on the craft of acting. I’m eager to explore a wide range of roles in film, TV, theater, and commercial work, and I’m excited to branch out into new genres and experiences.

In addition to my acting experience, I studied Music Technology with a major in Stage Performing Arts for 2 years , and I have full documentation of all my final projects from that time. This technical training complements my stage performance and has given me a comprehensive understanding of both the artistic and technical sides of the industry.

I was also part of a gospel drama group form 2011 to 2020 , where I won 4 "Card Awards," including Best Actress  (twice), Best Dressed, and Best Minister. These awards reflect my dedication to the craft, and I’m incredibly proud of them.

I’m looking forward to collaborating on a wide range of acting roles in the UK’s vibrant and inclusive creative industry, and I’m actively seeking potential employers who are willing to support visa sponsorships for skilled performers like me.

If you have any leads or know of any production companies, agents, or casting opportunities, I would love to hear from you! Please feel free to DM me or comment below.

Thank you so much for your time and consideration. I look forward to connecting with you all!

North East humans! 
I'm taking bookings for headshots and things 😊 
Get in touch! 😁

sharedPost.text:
Hey lovelies!! 

I'm taking bookings for October 😁 🌼🍂🍁🦊🎃

Need a bit of a spooky promo shoot for your brand? Send me your stuff! I'll get it sorted 😁 🎃🦊🍁

Need some updated headshots? Pop along to the studio and I'll be with you every step of the way! I love building up your confidence and taking you from being terrified to terrific! Honestly I've been told many times from many customers that I have a knack for bringing out the best in people and making them feel good about themselves - so you are in very safe hands! 

Got a spooky themed show coming up and need a quick Halloween promo shoot? Let's gather round the cauldron and cook up a plan 🎃 

Need some spooky scary stop motion for your little business?? Get in touch and we'll make a spooky story board! 

Don't be afraid to ask for a quote - I like to think I price fairly and prefer to do a sliding scale for different sized businesses. In the north east I'm very aware things can be tough for creatives! I also am a tiny business myself and put my heart and soul into everything I do, so please do not be afraid to ask!

Hello, 
My name is Jack Young. I am 23 and looking for some work. Don’t mind doing extras work as I’m starting out I would prefer that anyway. I am free on my days off work to do some filming please let me know if anybody has anything coming up or even this week and I meet the requirements. I am Male, 23, 6ft3, brown hair, medium build and starting out so very beginner. I do have a certificate in filmmaking however and so I have some experience in the process of it all and have worked on a tv show as an extra and behind the scenes on so far of three short films and I quite like the editing side of things. I will happily even be a runner for the day and don’t even necessarily need to be paid. 

Thankyou

items.text:
**Looking for 4 actors/actresses**

Hey everyone! 
We’re looking for **4 people who’d like to act** in a **camera and directing exercise** at our film school.
No previous experience needed, just enthusiasm and a willingness to collaborate.

**What it’s about:**
We’ll be working on **short dialogue scenes**, each focused on **a specific emotion**. The exercise will explore **camera movement** and how actors and directors adapt to each other, just like in a film, but with short and experimental scenes.

-Teaching in London out of Dance Attic Studios Fulham Broadway @danceatticstudios and ONLINE.

- Clients tend to have graduated from 3 year programs and leave with fundamental holes in their technique that they now want to fill. Is that you?

Chris Fung - Singing Teacher

sharedPost.text:
A HUGE thank you to everyone who has taken the time to apply, we’ve smashed the number of applicants we’ve had previously which is amazing! 😱
We’ve highlighted the key points to note:

📌 We’re a small agency and are incredibly busy at the moment, we appreciate people want to know but we cannot give updates throughout the screening process and replying to emails asking for information stops us being able to process applications

📌 If you have applied during the book opening period you will be notified whether successful or not but please bear with us as we work through applications

📌 Our social team have NO access to any information
regarding applications

📌 Our in person assessment day will be Sunday 19th October for successful applicants

📌 We will post on socials once we have contacted all applicants

📌 Also to clarify, you don’t get a confirmation email when you completed the application, if you were able to submit, it will have gone through. 🙂

And again thank you to everyone who took the time to apply we’ve got our fingers crossed for you all!
#thedramamob

Aktorka / statystka do krótkiego filmu – kampanii społecznej

📍 Miejsce: studio filmowe w Łodzi, ul. Krzemieniecka  (okolice Atlas Areny).

message.text:
HALLOWEEN CARNIVAL REHEARSALS 
📍 African Caribbean Centre
🗓️ Tuesdays, 6PM

We have always known that there is power in our movement. That our ancestors held on to something special!. We never just danced, or drummed, or sang, we commanded the elements! The  universe  submitted to our presence. We affected  cosmologies through our movement. 
They still don't understand how we did it., how carried magic and power through our movement.

Our classes are journey to commune with our heritage.
Together with Katumba, the Merseyside International Centre for Caribbean Carnival and Black Imagination are delivering a powerful Halloween experience. drum, dance, and ancestral Mas fused into living ritual. To be performed on the streets for the Halloween Parade.

REHEARSALS 
📍 African Caribbean Centre
🗓️ Tuesdays, 6PM

Step into the circle. Claim your culture!

items.text:
**STATYŚCI / DOROŚLI / DZIECI / WARSZAWA **

Hej, 

Na plan w Warszawie szukamy statystów:
* 9.10 - dorośli, w wieku 20-30 lat; naturalni - stawka, 130 zł.
* 10.10 - dorośli, w wieku 60+ - stawka, 130 zł.
* 10.10 - dzieci w wieku ok. 4 lat - stawka, 150 zł.
* 10.10 - dorośli, **najlepiej rodzice dzieciaków**, w różnym wieku - stawka, 130 zł.

Gdzie: Warszawa.

Kiedy: 9.10 lub 10.10.

Stawka: dzieci - 150 zł; dorośli - 130 zł.

***10.10 gramy na zewnątrz, na placu zabaw.**

**Zgłoszenia **proszę przesyłać na adres: wawa.statysci@gmail.com, w treści podając: imię i nazwisko, wiek, numer kontaktowy, miasto, aktualne zdjęcia oraz **koniecznie wzrost dzieci.**

Hej, 

Na plan w Warszawie szukamy statystów:
* 9.10 - dorośli, w wieku 20-30 lat; naturalni - stawka, 130 zł.
* 10.10 - dorośli, w wieku 60+ - stawka, 130 zł.
* 10.10 - dzieci w wieku ok. 4 lat - stawka, 150 zł.
* 10.10 - dorośli, **najlepiej rodzice dzieciaków**, w różnym wieku - stawka, 130 zł.

Gdzie: Warszawa.

Kiedy: 9.10 lub 10.10.

Stawka: dzieci - 150 zł; dorośli - 130 zł.

***10.10 gramy na zewnątrz, na placu zabaw.**

**Zgłoszenia **proszę przesyłać na adres: wawa.statysci@gmail.com, w treści podając: imię i nazwisko, wiek, numer kontaktowy, miasto, aktualne zdjęcia oraz **koniecznie wzrost dzieci.**

items.title: NAGRANIA SZUKAMY:

items.text:
Agencja Adliner Sp. z o.o. poszukuje lektorów - dzieci do animacji edukacyjnej 

Szczegóły: 
- nagranie w Warszawie prawdopodobnie pod koniec przyszłego tygodnia  
- lokalizacja nagrania - sadyba
- czas nagrania 2-3h 
- wynagrodzenie 500zł netto na Umowę o Dzieło (z przekazaniem praw bez ograniczeń czasowych na wszystkich polach eksploatacji) Jest to pierwsze z planowanej serii nagrań, więc jest możliwa kontynuacja współpracy 
- poszukujemy: 2 głosów chłopców i 3 głosów dziewczynek, w wieku 8 -13 lat 
- tematem nagrania jest ochrona środowiska, segregacja odpadów i recykling. W wyniku nagrania powstaną trzy krótkie animacje edukacyjne, które zostaną użyte w materiałach programu edukacyjnego kierowanego do szkół podstawowych.  

W celu zgłoszenia prosimy i wysłanie próbki głosu (nagranie telefonem) odczytującej poniższy tekst (odpowiednio dla chłopców i dla dziewczynek) na adres: [praca@adliner.pl](mailto:praca@adliner.pl) 
W tytule prosimy podać: "Głos chłopca/ dziewczynki do animacji edukacyjnej" a w zgłoszeniu prosimy o podanie danych kontaktowych rodzica (telefon komórkowy) 
Na zgłoszenia czekamy do 5 października 

Tekst dla Chłopców 
Dzieci są w fabryce papieru, Janek spogląda na duże bele z papierem i mówi: Wyglądają jak zwinięte latające dywany! Każdy papier ma taki kolor? Niebieski pojemnik jest początkiem drogi prowadzącej do prawdziwych skarbów!

Tekst dla dziewczynek
Dzieci są w zakładzie przetwarzania, przy maszynie separującej papier od plastik z opakowań wielomateriałowych.  
Ola mówi: Ale super! I nawet aż tak bardzo nie hałasuje. A nie lepiej od razu do właściwego pojemnika? Przecież to też jest kosz na odpady.

p.s. Proszę o niewysyłanie zgłoszeń w prywatnych wiadomościach

**[PAID CASTING CALL]**

We’re looking for warm and friendly Singaporeans students who commute regularly by public transport to be part of our upcoming social media content.

Shoot date: Wednesday, 08 Oct

Shoot time: Between 10:00am - 12:00pm

Time commitment: 2 hours

Talent fee: $100 per talent

**Who we need:**

Friendly individuals who are comfortable on camera (no acting experience required!) and who use public transport often, whether it’s going to school, visiting friends, family, or exploring new places.

items.text:
AMERIVENTS is Hiring!

We’re excited to assemble our Dream Team of talented professionals for iconic NYC events like SNL wrap parties, movie premieres, and sporting events.

**Building Our Dream Team**

At Amerivents, we are committed to assembling and empowering a "Dream Team" of talented individuals who bring diverse skills, shared values, and a unified purpose to every endeavor. Much like a championship sports team, we believe that our collective success is built on the strength and collaboration of our team members, each contributing their unique expertise to achieve exceptional results.

**Now Hiring FRONT OF HOUSE:**
* Catering Hospitality Staff
* Servers
* Bartenders
* Captains

**Now Hiring BACK OF HOUSE:**
* Dishwasher
* Utility
* Grill Cook
* Line Cook

**Requirements:**

2+ years of catering or high-end retail experience

You must be 18 or older

**Next Steps:**
1. Complete the interview survey here: [https://forms.gle/r3B2ib3kssxRfF5v8](https://forms.gle/r3B2ib3kssxRfF5v8)
2. Visit[ www.amerivents.com](http://www.amerivents.com/) and click “Apply” (mention “CORE-NYC” in the referral box).

**Why Amerivents?**
* Fast-paced, exciting, and team-oriented work environment
* Flexible schedules—you choose your availability!
* Gain unforgettable experiences in the hospitality industry
* Experience unique and inspiring event locations!

**What We’re Looking For:**
* 2+ years of catering or high-end retail experience
* Professional, adaptable, and radiate positivity team players
* Composure under pressure and ability to adapt to dynamic environments
* Flexible and reliable team players who can seamlessly adjust to varying roles and tasks
* Ability to lift 50 lbs and stand for extended periods

**To Our Team:**
We offer the chance to pursue your passions while contributing to a company that values your unique talents and provides the support you need to excel.

We look forward to hearing from you!

**This is not an official job offer**

items.text:
CASTING CALL

Production Company: GreenHouse Films Production

Project Type: BFA Short Film

Union Status: Non-Union

Pay Status: Unpaid Projected

Shooting Dates: TBD

Shooting Location: Orlando area

Summary: A lonely girl shunned by her school finds comfort in plants and in the one friend who truly sees her.

We have not set an exact shoot date, but we plan to begin filming sometime in November. This is an unpaid project - copy and credit will be given to all involved. This is a non-union production.

Character Breakdowns:

MONOMAY: Female, Late Teens (20s), A teen girl marked by facial scars and iris coloboma, finds purpose and comfort in tending to her beloved plants.

JASON: Male, Late Teens (20s), The school's "Golden Boy" athlete, hides his insecurities behind charisma.

FAN CLUB: Any gender, Teens (20s), A group of students that fawn over Jason and seek his attention.

How to Submit: Please send an email to greenhousefilmsproduction@gmail.com to reserve a time slot for auditions.

items.text:
So proud to be the Executive Producer and Casting Director on Taro O'Halloran’s Short Horror Film  HUMANZEE starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton as Ziggy!! 

It is screening at Screamfest Horror Film Festival in Hollywood at Mann’s Chinese Theatre!

sharedPost.text:
Congratulations to Taro O'Halloran of Weymouth High School Class of 2020 on the screening of his Short Horror Film Humanzee starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton of Weymouth at Screamfest Horror Film Festival at the @TCL Chinese Theater in Hollywood!  

I am so honored to have the titles of Executive Producer and Casting Director on this film!

The hope is someone will see it and want to develop it into a Full Length Feature Film!

I see this film bringing home some awards!

My fingers are crossed for Taro’s Team!

Thank you Diane Purdy's Children's Theatre Workshop for giving me my own Stage from 9 to 49 and for letting me pass it on to John and Jake who brought Taro home from school one day and we all collaborated on multiple video productions with Diane’s costumes for years!

Casting Call

Production: Mother's Ruin, by Steve Bird (Back by popular demand!)

The story so far in the life of Liverpool comedian Garry Skyner, one of Britain's first- born victims of the Thalidomide medical disaster. Steve Birds play is a moving and emotional, yet hard hitting play about the highs, lows, struggles and sheer determination of a loving Mother and her son who refused to be beaten by the Government and company that profited from this medical disaster.

We are looking for a talented female actor playing range 20-30ys, who is from Liverpool or can do a convincing accent, for the lead role of Frances, Gary's Mum.
Frances is a spirited, humourous woman, who whilst having a heart of gold, has an inner strength, is tough, and fights for her child and what is right.
If you believe you are what we are looking for please send you CV and headshot to elainestewart46@yahoo.com 

Auditions to take place on Sunday 21st September 1pm-3pm at a Liverpool venue to be disclosed on receipt of CV, and a script will be provided. 

Performances will take place at the Epstein Theatre on 27th and 28th February 2026.

You must be available for rehearsals Sundays 1pm- 4pm (in Liverpool) starting 2nd November.
*This is a profit share production

It's part of a brand-new UK theatre tour coming in 2026, and this will be one of our headline public marketing stunts. 

The role is simple, but really important:

. Filming the event (reactions) on a phone (2 people required)

What you'll get:

. Travel expenses covered

. Be part of an unusual, exciting event that's going to get a lot of attention

. Something different to talk about (and looks great on a CV for anyone in events, film, or theatre)

If you're free, reliable, and up for being part of something mysterious and fun, drop me a message here or comment below and I'll share the details.

Thanks! 

Charlie

items.text:
**CASTING CALL — BL REALITY DATING SERIES (PAID)**

**Synopsis:**

Six gay men spend one day together under the same roof, exploring love and identity through every colour of the rainbow! 

Inspired by the six colours of Pride (life, healing, sunlight, nature, serenity and spirit), will the boys find a spark or something real along the way?

**What we’re looking for:**

Singapore-based gay men (18+) who are

🌈Comfortable being yourself on camera

🌈Open to meeting new people, sharing your thoughts

🌈Down to have fun and be part of something authentic

🌈Different looks, backgrounds, and personalities welcome — come as you are!

**Interested? Reach out to us at casting@250films.co by 30 Nov 2025 with:**

🌈Name

🌈Age

🌈Height

🌈Recent photos/headshots

🌈Intro video (recorded within the past month) — tell us who you are, what your dating life’s like, best/worst first date, ideal first date, whatever feels you!

🌈 Socials (if you’d like)

**If shortlisted, we’ll set up a quick call to chat and get to know you better!**

**Commitment for casted applicants: **

1-day shoot in January, exact date TBC!

Possibly a casual meet-up with the production crew before filming, just to say hi!

MK44 3QP & MK17 8UE
📆 Contract: December 2025
💸 Rate: £20 per hour

• Entry-level acting skills

• Basic script work and immersive performance ability

• Confident group singing of children’s Christmas songs
