😲Amazingly flexible! Stunningly beautiful!🌸💫🌸

Such incredible skills! Honestly, it left me speechless.👏🏻🌷💝

🎟️ Visit https://1kb.link/gzbqY3 for information about a theater near you.

⚡️ Don’t miss your chance to witness the magic and grace of a live performance that will leave you breathless. 💫

🙋‍♀️ In Firebird Turn, the dancer would initiate the turn by kicking her leg back so high that it almost touches the crowd of her head. She would then maintain that hold while completing her turns. Under this graceful move lies a combination of strength, flexibility and coordination that takes countless hours to perfect.

📲 Tag a friend who needs to see this with you! 💖

items.text:
Bottle Girls 🍾
I'm looking for 6 confident and curvy bottle girls to join our team for a 3 month contract running from early November to the end of January.

Details:
 • Location: Lagos, Nigeria
 • Return flights and accommodation will be provided
 • Must be available to start in early November
 • Must have a curvy figure and a fun, outgoing personality

If you’re interested, please send me a direct message including:
 1. Your current location
 2. Recent photos (to be shared with the client for selection)

It’s a great short-term opportunity to be part of an exciting venue and event season in Lagos!

Warszawa! Na plan serialu Gliniarze poszukujemy epizodystów: 
Jarosław Janas (37) - mundurowy z komisariatu dzielnicy, gdzie grasują złodzieje. Sympatyczny, pomocny, profesjonalny i zaangażowany policjant. 
 
Data: 24.10
Stawka: 350 zł netto
 
·       Krzywy (19) - „herszt” bandy młodocianych przestępców. Zbuntowany nastolatek z trudnej rodziny. Tatuaże, siłownia - sprawny fizycznie, wysportowany, pościgi i ucieczka nie sprawiają mu problemów. 
 
Data: 22. i 23.10
Stawka: 1200 zł netto za całość
 
·       Muras (20) - członek bandy Krzywego. „Kaskader” posiadający umiejętność wyczynowej jazdy na rowerze. 
 
Data: 22. i 23.10
Stawka: 1200 zł netto za całość
 
·       Sonik (20) - członek bandy Krzywego. „Kaskader” posiadający umiejętność wyczynowej jazdy na rowerze. 
 
Data: 22. i 23.10
Stawka: 1200 zł netto za całość
 
·       Paser (44) - notowany recydywista, nie dbający jakoś przesadnie o wygląd czy kondycję fizyczną, skupiony na lewych interesach.
 
Data:  23.10
Stawka: 250 zł netto
 
·       Sebek (16) - ofiara przestępców, kadet z klubu judo Adama. Sympatyczny chłopak. 
 
Data:  23.10
Stawka: 250 zł netto
 
·       Mama Sebka (44) - przejęta losem syna matka. Płacząca, pełna empatii, troskliwa. Konieczne PRAWO JAZDY
 
Data:  22. i 23.10
Stawka: 700 zł netto za całość
 
·       Matka Kamy (42) - przejęta losem córki matka. Nieco nerwowa, porywcza, ale kochająca i troskliwa. 
 
Data:  24.10
Stawka: 200 zł netto
 
 
Chętne osoby zapraszam do wysyłania zgłoszeń na adres: casting.outset@interia.pl
W tytule maila proszę o wpisanie nazwy postaci.
W treści maila proszę o zawarcie następujących informacji:
1.           Wiek/wzrost/waga
2.           Nr tel. Do kontaktu
3.           Krótki opis doświadczenia
4.           Linki do sowich materiałów video – demo/wizytówka/scenki castingowe
5.           Aktualne zdjęcie
6.           Informacje o posiadanym i czynnym prawie jazdy lub jego braku
7.           Inormacje o ukończonej szkole aktorskiej/kursach
Nie zwracamy kosztów dojazdu/noclegu

topComments.text: Szkoda, że nie zwracacie. Będzie Wam trudniej znaleźć.

items.text:
ARE YOU AN ACTOR STUCK IN YOUR HEAD???

Yep... same. But I’ve been training with Steve Eastin and it’s honestly flipping everything upside down for me. You’ve seen this guy, he’s in like 200 movies [Catch Me If You Can, Con Air, Field of Dreams, Matchstick Men, etc.].

Not a lot of people even realize he’s teaching again. Feels like some random secret I lucked into.

What he does is just… different. Really different. Not about analyzing or breaking stuff down. It’s not gonna be for everyone but if you’re someone like me who gets trapped in overthinking, this is the kind of work that yanks you out of your head and dumps you right into the moment. If you live for those times where it feels like something else is taking over and you’re just along for the ride, this is that.

It’s rooted in Charles Conrad’s whole “choiceless awareness” thing. Basically stripping your brain of anything to hang onto and forcing you to just respond. No scene breakdowns, no making sure “beats” land. Just keeping it alive and messy and letting the work happen through you. If you’re curious, this article explains it better:

[[https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/](https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/)](https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/something-think-64356/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

Class is super bare bones. Sit across, cold read, memorize, toss it, repeat. Just working the muscle of not thinking. Everything’s filmed so you’re used to being on camera too.

And the wild part, Conrad literally handpicked Steve to carry this forward. He taught for decades, everyone in casting knew his people, then he retired. And now he just randomly opened these tiny classes at his house. They’re small, intimate, and honestly feel like something that shouldn’t still exist.

If this even slightly calls to you, it’s a rare shot.

Classes here:

[[https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/)](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

Η μέθοδος απευθύνεται σε **όλους** όσους επιθυμούν να βιώσουν τη μαγεία των ρόλων και περιλαμβάνει:

items.text: Registration for this FREE webinar now open!

sharedPost.text:
I’ve been a model and actor for over 30 years, and as a certified mindset coach, I’ve also had the privilege of helping my daughter strengthen her mindset and grow her career with co-star, supporting, and supporting lead roles in projects for Paramount +, CBS, Hallmark, and more. Most recently, she appears as Rachel in Amazon Prime’s Top 10* *show* The Runarounds*.

﻿

I've been asked a lot over the years to share my experience and help other parents and young actors along on their acting journeys; that’s why I’m hosting a **free webinar on October 19** where you'll learn:
* Mindset strategies I taught my daughter (and use with my actor clients)
* The realities of building a career in acting—what most people *don’t*tell you
* The pros and cons of pursuing an acting degree
* Strategies we've used to open up audition and booking opportunties
* PLUS: get the inside scoop as my daughter shares her experience on *The Runarounds*: from first audition to being on set.

🎟️ Don't wait! Get all the details and save your spot here → [[Register Now]](https://campaign-statistics.com/link_click/e9VEqJ-gpxZ2D6-4ysUg9/a85533005915d0327bef8a6796583a43)

﻿

📅 **Date: October 19, 2025 **

🕔 **Time:** **4:00pm-5:30pm EST**

﻿

While this webinar is geared towards young actors & their parents, **actors of all levels **will benefit from this session. We will have an open, honest conversation that gives you clarity, direction, and encouragement as you navigate the acting journey.

﻿

Hope to see you there!

I’d love to connect, please feel free to reach out!

Tony 🙂
